# Client → Convex API: https://YOUR_DEPLOYMENT.convex.cloud (Settings → URL, not the dashboard link).
VITE_CONVEX_URL=

# Convex Auth: set on EACH Convex deployment (Dashboard → Settings → Environment variables, or `pnpm exec convex env set`).
# SITE_URL = where the browser lands after OAuth. Must match the site users actually open:
#   dev deployment: http://localhost:5173
#   prod deployment: https://notes.gayle.dev   (NOT localhost — or sign-in will redirect there)
# CONVEX_SITE_URL is usually https://YOUR_DEPLOYMENT.convex.site (JWT issuer + OAuth callback host); set on the same deployment if missing.
#
# Allowlist (convex/allowlist.ts): backend only reads deployment env, not this file. Example:
# pnpm exec convex env set AUTHED_USERS '["you@example.com"]'
# or: pnpm exec convex env set ALLOWED_EMAILS you@example.com,friend@example.com
#
# OAuth / sessions also need RS256 keys on the deployment (JWT_PRIVATE_KEY + JWKS). Generate and set them with:
#   pnpm dlx @convex-dev/auth
# (interactive; includes this step) or create a keypair once and `pnpm exec convex env set` both values.
